reviews.review_text:
Not to be missed... Actually... transferred by Doug Mow. 
EAC through FLAC16 by Alex Ford.

Thanks I have been looking for a decent recording of this show.  I was there and Jerry was sharp that evening.  For historical accuracy the venue is called the Onondaga County War Memorial Auditorium.
Another Solid Show Well played, but no standout highlights

Credit where credit is due Excellent audience recording of quite a fine show.  Thirteen songs in the first set and a genuinely jammed second set.  Pretty tight top to bottom.  The Boys pretty quickly reached a peak with Brent and this is a show from that plateau -  he is fully present for this performance. 

About the credit due - Unlike Satisfaction, The Last Time is not a Rolling Stones song.  It was written by the late great Bobby Womack and one of his sisters - theirs was a very musical family.  He has an amazing body of work in addition to this song - check it out.  You are right about Stones covers they are rare.  Don't overlook JGB covering Moonlight Mile back in the day, like Keystone Berkeley back in the day.  Jerry definitely related to that one!
